cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning algorithms and their application in complex environments with sparse feedback. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses deep neural networks for learning, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of intrinsic motivation, which is a topic of interest in the field of computational neuroscience and could lead to it being categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
